# GDS-VERO compliance — mandatory for UI work

When you **create or materially change React UI** (`.tsx` / `.jsx`):

1. **Follow** the **GDS-VERO compliance review** section in `node_modules/@gds-vero/react/GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md` (stack, imports, Chakra v3, semantic tokens, vero surfaces, typography, responsive layout, **component API verified against GDS docs**).
2. **Before writing compound components** (`Accordion`, `Dialog`, `Tabs`, `Menu`, `Field`, …): open the GDS docs page (https://tomiputto.github.io/gds-vero/) — do **not** guess slot names from memory.
3. **Complete the checklist** in that section before finishing. Fix violations in code when you can.
4. **Run `npm run lint` or `pnpm lint`** and fix errors on touched files.
5. **End every UI delivery** with the full **Delivery audit report** from the agent guide §3 — all categories and **Compliance Status** (PASS / WARNING / FAIL). Do **not** skip or shorten.

Common fixes: **`GDSButton`** in **`GDSProvider`**; card CTA inline (no `width="full"` except login); `VeroAppShell` + `VeroPageLayout`; `Breadcrumb` above `h1`; verified: **Accordion**, **Dialog**, **Tabs**, **Field**, **Card**, **Button**, **Page layout**, **Breadcrumb**, **VeroMainHeader**.
